Displacement Meter - A metering instrument in which mechanical displacement of known volume chambers are repeatedly filled and emptied; the volume of the chambers times the cycles of displacement is equal to the measure of volume; "Displacement Meter" terminology may also be used to define the application of volume calculation

Flange Tap - A critical parameter of design for orifice measurement where the pressure ports for the sensing of static and differential pressure are located one inch upstream and one inch downstream of the orifice plate; "Flange Tap" terminology is used to define the tap configuration employed

Mercury Meter - A type of recording instrument which employs mercury displacement in a fixed chamber when pressure is applied, the displacement is an indicator of the pressure applied; the mercury recorder is primarily used in low pressure differential pressure measurement; "Mercury Meter" terminology is used to indicate that corrections is volume calculations are applied with respect to mercury recorder characteristics

Orifice Meter - A metering instrument used to measure flowing fluid through a pipe by velocity displacement and employing orifice technologies; the orifice meter is an inferential device which senses the pressure differential created by the passage of a fluid through an orifice of critical diameter placed in the pipe; a rate of flow is calculated from the fluid flowing and instrument parameters to determine the measure of volume; "Orifice Meter" terminology may also be used to define the application of volume calculation

Pipe Tap - A critical parameter of design for orifice measurement where the pressure ports for the sensing of static and differential pressure are located in a distance of two and one-half times the published inside diameter of the meter upstream of the orifice place and a distance of eight times the published inside diameter of the meter downstream of the orifice plate; "Pipe Tap" terminology is used to define the tap configuration employed

Turbine Meter - A type of metering instrument used to measure flowing fluid through a pipe by velocity displacement and employing turbine senses the rotation of a rotor axis turbine which is parallel to the axis of flow and proportional to the rate; the measure of volume is determined by counting the revolutions of the rotor; "Turbine Meter" terminology may also be used to define the application of volume calculation

Tinting Strength - A measure of the hiding power of a titanium dioxide sample obtained by comparing the green (Y) reflectance of a tinted waterbased formula against that of a standard
Emulsion Gloss - The 60-degree gloss of a pigment sample in a waterbased paint formula

Gas-to-Oil Ratio - A measure of the gas produced from a hydrocarbon well relative to the oil produced

Hydroxyl Number - The alkalinity of oil, fat, wax or other substances

Jominy Hardenability - The product's hardness and depth of hardening

Lights - A relative term that is used to identify the weight percent of all molecules below the peak identified as the molecule being tested for in a gas chromatograph result; also, all molecules that have a boiling point lower than the molecule being tested

Pipe Tap - A critical parameter of design for orifice measurement where the pressure ports for the sensing of static and differential pressure are located in a distance of two and one-half times the published inside diameter of the meter upstream of the orifice place and a distance of eight times the published inside diameter of the meter downstream of the orifice plate; "Pipe Tap" terminology is used to define the tap configuration employed

Turbine Meter - A type of metering instrument used to measure flowing fluid through a pipe by velocity displacement and employing turbine senses the rotation of a rotor axis turbine which is parallel to the axis of flow and proportional to the rate; the measure of volume is determined by counting the revolutions of the rotor; "Turbine Meter" terminology may also be used to define the application of volume calculation

Inclusion Rating - The internal nonmetallic particles in the product
Jominy Hardenability - The product's hardness and depth of hardening

Lights - A relative term that is used to identify the weight percent of all molecules below the peak identified as the molecule being tested for in a gas chromatograph result; also, all molecules that have a boiling point lower than the molecule being tested
Low Propagation Delay Time - The time between the specified reference points on the input and output waveforms, with the output changing from high level to the defined low level
Lethal Concentration, 50% ("LC-50") - The lowest value of concentration which will result in the death of exactly one half of a given biological test population
Lethal Dose, 50% ("LD-50") - The lowest value of dose which will result in the death of exactly one half of a given biological test population
Limited Dome Height (LDH) - Response to simulated drawing operation
Leaf - Percentage of leaf in fiber as determined by trash count and trash area
Liquid Injection Test Rate - Volume of liquids, such as oil, mud, and water, which are injected into the well during a 24-hour test period
Limit Intrinsic Viscosity - The percent of cellulose in a crystalline rather than amorphous form
Loss on Ignition - Loss (of material) that occurs when a sample is ignited
Loss on Drying - The amount of material lost after heating to a constant weight at a specified temperature
Low Boilers - The components of a mixture which boil at a lower temperature than the rest of the mixture
Line Pressure - Fluid pressure of the production line between the well and the separator unit or gathering line
Length Shrinkage - The amount of shrinkage occurring per linear yard of fabric expressed in percentage
Linear Sheet Swelling - The increased size of a sheet of pulp when immersed in caustic during pulping
Liner Top Depth - Depth below the surface of the top of a liner string; liner is a tube within the casing used to separate different strata but does not extend to the surface
Melt Range - A range of temperatures used to identify at what point compounds start to transform from a solid to a liquid state
Maximum Differential Pressure - The largest differential pressure reading at which this device will measure the differential pressure accurately
Maximum Static Pressure - Largest flowing gas pressure at which this device will measure volumes accurately
Maturity - Swelling and compression of fiber
Measurement Voltage - The reference voltage level on AC waveforms for determining AC performance
Maximum Input Low Voltage - The guaranteed input low threshold
Melt Time - The time between the first appearance of liquid and the total disappearance of solid
Efficient Rate-Reservoir - The maximum daily oil or gas withdrawal rate from a hydrocarbon reservoir
Minimum Input High Voltage - The guaranteed input high voltage
Highest Torque - Highest torque attained during specified period of time when no plateau or maximum torque is obtained
Micronaire - Fiber fineness; the higher the value, the courser the fiber
Moisture - The amount of water in an item
Production Rate-Well - The maximum daily rate of at which oil or gas may be produced from a hydrocarbon well
MCQuaid - Austenitic grain morphology of a sample
Module R (R Bar) - Ratio of true width strain to true thickness strain; indicates the ability of the material to resist thinning and deform in draw
Maximum Total Depth - Total distance along the well bore to the final bottom hole location
Mullen - The energy required to burst a sheet with one of several standard pluggers
Neutralization Number - The quantity of acid or base required to neutralize basic or acidic constituents in a substance
Number of Items per Package Label
Number of Splices per Package Label
Nil Ductility Test - The condition required to initiate brittle fracture
Number of Sheets per Package Label
Net Net Weight - The weight of an item exclusive of the weight of any shipping packaging and of any additional packaging or attachments such as cellophane wrapping or hangers
Non-Volatile Matter - The amount of residue remaining after an analytical process
NOx Emissions Performance - Difference in exhaust NOx emissions attributed to a gasoline formulation as compared to the 1990 baseline gasoline
N Value - The work hardening rate capability of material and predicts the ability to deform in stretch, plane strain, and bending
Output Low Voltage - The maximum guaranteed low voltage at an output terminal sinking the specified load-current output low current
Oil/Condensate Gravity - Production fluid density relative to the density of water
Oil/Condensate Test Rate - Volume of oil and natural gas condensate produced during a 24-hour test period
Odor - The quality of a substance that stimulates the olfactory organ
Output Low Current - The current flowing into an output which is in the low state
Output High Voltage - The minimum guaranteed high voltage at an output terminal for the specified output current 'output high current' and at the minimum VCC value
Output High Current - The leakage current flowing into a turned-off, open-collector output with a specified high output voltage applied
Output Off Current Low - The current flowing out of a disabled three-state output with a specified low output voltage applied
Oil - Liquid, slippery, viscous, relatively nonvolatile chemical
Output Off Current High - The current flowing into a disabled three-state output with a specified high output voltage applied
Output Short-Circuit Current - The current flowing out of an output which is in the high state when that output is short circuit to ground

Output Disable Time from Low Level of a 3-State Output - The delay time between the specified reference points on the input and output voltage waveforms with the three-state output changing from the low level to a high impedance 'off' state

Output Disable Time from High Level of a 3-State Output - The delay time between the specified reference points on the input and output voltage waveforms with three-state output changing from the high level to a high impedance 'off' state

Output Enable Time from Low Level of a 3-State Output - The delay time between the specified reference points on the input and output voltage waveforms with the three-state output changing from the high impedance 'off' state to the low level

Output Enable Time from High Level of a 3-State Output - The delay time between the specified reference points on the input and output voltage waveforms with the three-state output changing from high impedance 'off' state to the high level
Organic Carbon - The amount of carbon which is bonded to another carbon or hydrogen or both
Others Each - Identifies the maximum value of any single metallic element not listed in the chemical composition limits standard
Others Total - Identifies the total value of all metallic elements not listed in the chemical composition limits standard
Oxidizable Substance - Represents the amount of a substance that can undergo oxidation
Oxidizing Substance - A substance which removes electrons from other substances
Particle Size - The diameter of solid and liquid particles
Plug Back Total Depth - Well depth after plug back operations to abandon a lower producing horizon or formation
Casing/Liner Tubing Depth - Depth to the bottom of the casing/liner string
Pump Depth from Ground - The distance from the ground surface to the subsurface pump unit
Magnetic Permeability - The ease with which a material can be magnetized and how much better it is as a path for magnetic fields than air
Perforation Feet Open - Linear distance of all perforations of the well casing string
Pulse Setup Time - The interval immediately preceding the active transition of the timing or preceding the transition of the control input to its latching level
Hardwood Fiber - The amount of threadlike, primarily cellulosic material derived from the wood portion of hardwood trees
Pulse Hold Time - The interval immediately following the active transition of the timing pulse or following the transition of control input to its latching level
Pulse Width - The time between the specified reference points on the leading and trailing edges of a pulse

Pulse Recovery Time - The time between the reference point on the trailing edge of an asynchronous input control pulse and the reference point on the activating edge of a synchronous pulse input such that the device will respond to the synchronous input
Percent of Order (-, +) - Expression of allowable variance of order expressed either as absolute (for example 92% to 110%) or relative percent (for example - 8% to + 10%)
Pour Point - The lowest temperature at which an oil is observed to flow when cooled
Proprietary Shade - Identifies to customers when a textile company is using the customer's proprietary shade code versus the standard industry shade code
Processability - A rating of the ability to process
Softwood Fiber - The amount of threadlike, primarily cellulosic material derived from the wood of softwood trees
Relative Fraction of Pure Long-Chain Cellulose - The ratio by weight of pure long-chain and degraded cellulose to pulp where cellulose molecules of various chain lengths occur
Relative Fraction of Total Cellulose - The ratio by weight of total cellulose to pulp
Reactivity - The rate at which a substance reacts or the amount of substance that reacts
Reducing Substance - A substance which donates electrons to other substances
Refining - The severity of mechanical processing stage expressed by the amount of energy applied and length of time product is retained within equipment
Refractive Index - The ratio of the velocity of light in a vacuum to the velocity of light in the liquid
Reflectance - The fraction of the total radiant flux incident upon a surface that is reflected and that varies according to the wavelength distribution of the incident variation

Resistance - The property of a conductor causing electric energy to be transformed into heat; equal to the voltage across the conductor divided by the electrical current flowing in the conductor; measured in ohms
Usage Deviation (Applies to Kilowatt Hours, Kilowatt Demand and Reactive Demand)
Site Atmospheric Pressure - Ambient pressure of the metering location
Pulp Impurities - The percent hemicellulose polysaccharides and degraded cellulose in pulp fibers
Start - Identifies a value measured at the start of a testing process or range of test results
Hemicellulose - The percent hemicellulose polysaccharides in pulp fibers
Saponification Number - The number of milligrams of potassium hydroxide that is consumed by 1 gram of sample
Slit Width - Width into which a customer wants a material slit (cut) length wise
Supply Current - The current flowing into the VCC supply terminal of the circuit with specified input conditions and open outputs
Solderability - A measure of the ability of a material or component to be soldered
Slagging Index - The result of a procedure for obtaining information regarding the accumulation of ash deposits on radiant heat exchange surfaces in the furnace
SAM-B Rating - Measures cleanliness of steel for critical parts as to B-oxide volume in the steel
SAM-D Rating - Measures cleanliness of steel for critical parts as to D-oxide volume in the steel
Solids - The non-volatile material remaining after an analytical process
Softening Range - The temperature range in which material without a melting point goes from a rigid to a soft condition
Separator Pressure - Operating pressure of the oil/water/gas separating unit
Stability - The property of a chemical compound which is not readily decomposed and does not react with other compounds
Staple - Conventional method of measuring fiber length as pulled by hand
Suspended Matter - The mixture of fine, non-settling particles of a solid within a liquid or gas
Surface Tension - The force acting on the surface of a liquid which tends to minimize the area of the surface
S10 Minus S18 Value - The percent degraded cellulose in pulp fibers
Single End Break - Break point of a single strand of yarn expressed in grams
Skein Break - Break strength of yarn in skein form
T50 - Temperature at which 50% of the volume of a mixture being distilled has been evaporated
T90 - Temperature at which 90% of the volume of a mixture being distilled has been evaporated
Taste - The chemical sense by which flavors are perceived depending on taste, tactile, and warm and cold receptors in the mouth, as well as smell receptors in the nose
Perforation Top Depth - The depth from the ground surface to the top, or shallowest, portion of the well casing perforations
Texture - The property of a solid substance which is dependent on the size, form, order, and grouping of the smaller parts of which it is made and the way in which these parts are united
Torque - A force that produces rotation or torsion
Toxic Emissions Performance - Difference in exhaust toxic emissions attributed to a gasoline formulation as compared to the 1990 baseline gasoline

Tubing Pressure - Flowing - Fluid pressure within the inner tubing used to isolate different production streams from the surrounding well while production is flowing from the well; measured during well testing and completion operations

Tubing Pressure - Shutin - Fluid pressure within the casing, the outermost tubing used to isolate the well from the surrounding geology, with the well annulus closed; measured during well testing and completion operations
Trash Area - The number of pixels dotted by trash
Trash Count - Amount of trash in the court fiber
Transmittance - The fraction of the emitted light of a given wavelength which is not reflected or absorbed but passes through a substance
Turbidity - The extent of cloudiness in an item in which colloidally dispersed particles are present
Maximum True Vertical Depth - Total vertical distance from a surface location directly above the bottom hole location
Cube - The external cubic dimensions of a specified product
Uniformity - The degree of uniformity of fibers in a sample
Unknowns - Substances that are quantitated but of unknown identity
Vinyl - A chemical having the vinyl group CH2=CH-
VOC Emissions Performance - Difference in exhaust VOC (Volatile Organic Compounds) emissions attributed to a gasoline formulation as compared to the 1990 baseline gasoline
Volatiles - The gas or vapor material given off by an item under defined conditions
Water Depth - The depth of the water at an offshore location; measured from sea or lake bottom to the mean tidal level
Weight Loss - The amount of substance by weight that a material loses when subjected to specified conditions
Water-Oil Distribution Coefficient - A measure of the miscibility of oil and water
Wellhead Pressure-Flowing - The pressure as measured at the wellhead of a hydrocarbon well during a flow test
Wellhead Pressure Shutin - The pressure as measured at the wellhead of a hydrocarbon well during a shutin condition
Water Test Rate - The volume of water produced during a 24-hour test period
Width Shrinkage - The amount of shrinkage occurring per yard in the width of fabric expressed in percentage
Side Height, Flat Bed With Removable Sides
Yarn Count - The length per unit mass of yarn
Power Factor - Relationship between watts and volt - amperes necessary to supply electric load
N-Butane - Relative concentration of N-Butane in the gas stream being measured
